	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />For the true NES development experience, you'll need to learn 6502 assembly.  There are various assemblers to choose from.  They are listed on the nesdev main page.  I suggest you pickup a good 6502 assembly book and start reading. You can find them pretty cheap on amazon. Also, read the "Nintendo Entertainment System Documentation" document on the main page.  This will give you an overview of how the NES works. Finally, have a look at Michael Martin's "NES 101" tutorial on the main page.  It will give you an idea of how to get started.
<br />
<br />Hope this helps.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


