	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">Colino wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">I don't have to move (MOV) values between parts of memory to do a multiplication right?  <img src="./images/smilies/icon_lol.gif" alt=":lol:" title="Laughing" /></div>
<br />The 6502 is a very basic CPU, it doesn't even have built-in multiplication and division instructions, so if you really need those (you should avoid them as much as possible) you have to code your own routines, using bit shifting, additions and subtractions. There's definitely a lot of moving involved, although in 6502 assembly the terms are "load" (from memory) and "store" (to memory), not "move".

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


