<br />
<br />This is very true.  One of the pitfalls of 6502 for new comers is debugging.  Debugging NES code is harder to grasp than in high level languages (such as C++).  It can be very frustrating if you do not understand how the NES works internally.  You really have to know what your project code is doing at all times.

		

