		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I don't know much about actual books, because the 2 of them I had in my hands were pretty weak, and even had errors. Around here people suggest "Programming the 6502" by Rodnay Zaks a lot, so I guess it's probably one of the best books around.
<br />
<br />Personally, I learned from online material only. <a href="http://www.obelisk.demon.co.uk/6502/index.html" class="postlink">This</a> is an interesting introduction to the 6502. Don't forget to check <a href="http://6502.org/" class="postlink">http://6502.org/</a> for 6502 information.

		

